    • saveModifyBookingRoom

      public void saveModifyBookingRoom​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws java.io.IOException
      This code is a method that saves changes made to a booking room in a hotel management system. The method takes in an ActionEvent event and throws an IOException. It first initializes several variables and checks if certain fields are empty or contain non-integer values. If any of these fields are empty or contain non-integer values, a message is displayed to the user indicating that there are empty fields. Otherwise, a confirmation dialog is displayed to the user asking if they are sure they want to save the changes. If the user confirms, the method then creates a new bookingRooms object with the modified values and calls the ModifyBookingM method on that object. If the user does not confirm, a message is displayed indicating that the modification has been canceled. The method then switches to the booking room view.

    • translateDashboard

      public void translateDashboard​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      It is used to animate the sliding in and out of a dashboard menu on the user interface. The function is triggered by an ActionEvent.The function sets up a TranslateTransition animation, which will move the "sliderDashboard" node by a certain number of pixels along the x-axis. The distance and direction of the movement is determined by the value of the "postionDashboardSlider" variable, If the variable is 0, the animation will slide the dashboard in by moving it 173 pixels to the right. If the variable is 1, the animation will slide the dashboard out by moving it -173 pixels to the left. The transition animation will take 1 second to complete.
